GEN WAS ENRICHED TO 98.7 PERCENTAGES IN O-18.
. FLIGHT PATH=50 M.

THICK BY 36 CM IN DIAMETER BACKED BY 3 PHOTOMULTIPLIER

DATA WERE  CORRECTED FOR (A) THE DEAD-TIME AND (B) THE

x4freetext: STATISTICAL ERRORS OF MEASUREMENTS.
ENERGY  RESOLUTION OF SPECTROMETER WAS 10 KEV AT 2 MEV
NEUTRON ENERGY AND 200 KEV AT 10 MEV NEUTRON ENERGY.
THE NORMALIZATION  OF NEUTRON SPECTRA WAS ACCOMPLISHED
BY  NORMALIZING  TO AN EQUAL NUMBER  OF PHOTONS IN THE
CORRESPONDING BREMSSTRAHLUNG INTENSITY DISTRIBUTION IN
A 50 KEV WIDE BIN AT 9 MEV.
. THE RATIO OF THE 2S1/2 TO 1D5/2 CONFIGURATION
AMPLITUDES IN THE GROUND STATE OF O-18 WAS OBTAINED.
PHOTONEUTRON ENERGY SPECTRA FROM O-18 HAVE BEEN MEASU-
RED AT BREMSSTRAHLUNG ENDPOINT ENERGIES FROM 11 TO  18
MEV  IN 1 MEV STEPS  TO OBTAIN  THE GROUND STATE CROSS
SECTION AND THE FIRST EXCITED STATE CROSS SECTION.
.DATA WERE COMPILED IN SCJAD OF SARATOV STATE
UNIVERSITY.

x4freetext: THE GROUND STATE CROSS SECTION.
EXCITATION ENERGY AFTER EMISSION OF NE-
UTRON.
FOR EACH ENDPOINT ENERGY  A SPECTRUM OF  PHOTONEUTRONS
FROM  DEUTERIUM WAS OBTAINED. AFTER CONVERSION OF EACH
OF  THE DEUTERIUM SPECTRA  TO THE EFFICIENCY CORRECTED
ENERGY SPECTRA, THE SHAPES OF THE BREMSSTRAHLUNGS INT-
ENSITY DISTRIBUTIONS WERE DETERMINED  BY DIVIDING THEM
BY THE DEUTRON CROSS SECTION. BY DIVIDING THE O-18 NE-
UTRON SPECTRA BY THE CORRESPONDING BREMSSTRAHLUNG DIS-
TRIBUTIONS, THE PSEUDOGROUND STATE CROSS SECTIONS WERE
OBTAINED USING Q-VALUE OF 8.05 MEV FOR THE GROUND STA-
TE. TO OBTAIN THE GROUND STATE CROSS SECTION ONLY  THE
TIP REGION OF 1 MEV OF EACH SPECTRUM WAS USED. THE TIP
REGIONS OF THE  PSEUDOGROUND STATE CROSS SECTIONS WERE
COMBINED TO OBTAIN THE GROUND STATE CROSS SECTION AS A
FUNCTION OF EXCITATION ENERGY.

x4freetext: THE  FIRST  EXCITED  STATECROSS SECTION.
EXCITATION ENERGY AFTER EMISSION OF NE-
UTRON.
THE CROSS SECTION TO THE FIRST EXCITED STATE WAS EXTR-
ACTED  FROM  THE DATA BY FIRST  MULTIPLYING THE GROUND
STATE CROSS SECTION BY EACH SUCCESSIVE  BREMSSTRAHLUNG
DISTRIBUTION. THIS PRODUCED A SET OF NORMALIZED NEUTR-
ON SPECTRA ( CONTAINING THE GROUND STATE  CONTRIBUTION
ONLY). SUBTRACTION OF EACH SPECTRUM FROM THE CORRESPO-
NDING MEASURED NEUTRON SPECTRUM EXTRACTED NEUTRON CON-
TRIBUTIONS FROM TRANSITIONS TO THE EXCITED STATES. DI-
VISION BY THE RESPECTIVE BREMSSTRAHLUNG  DISTRIBUTIONS
PRODUCED PSEUDO EXCITED CROSS SECTIONS  WHEN A Q-VALUE
OF 8.92 MEV WAS USED.THE FIRST EXCITED STATE CROSS SE-
CTION WAS THEN DETERMINED FOLLOWING THE SAME PROCEDURE
AS FOR THE GROUND STATE CROSS SECTION , BUT USING HERE
A TIP REGION OF 1.6 MEV.
